on. The large scale projects, thegrand expos and the busing streets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had. My family and I left Dubai in 2009 following the 2008 recession.<br />\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" width="1003" height="194" /></p>\n<h2>Life in Tunisia</h2>\n<p>Far the busy five-laned roads and the sky piercing buildings, the city of Sousse is a quiet and costal city in Tunisia. The quiet however did not remain for long. A year after I moved to Sousse the Tunisian Revolution, nicknamed the "Revolution of the Jasmines", broke out. I witnessed the protests, heard the gunfire and participated in protecting our neighborhood.</p>\n<p>Neither my studies nor my moral were hindered due to the move and the subsequent revolution. On the contrary they were strengthened.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-296" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r.png 425w" alt="" width="300" height="160" /></p>\n<h2>Life inEgypt</h2>\n<p>Despite having lived in and visited Egypt, I did not know much of what Egypt has to offer. Gaining acceptance to AUC triggered a process of discovering what I hitherto considered familiar. Underneath the political turmoil and economic instability is a thriving and diverse population that calls for unity and prosperity. I am still uncovering the secrets of Egypt. Who knows what I will discover?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To Education</p>\n";s:10:"margin_top";s:0:"";s:17:"margin_top_medium";s:0:"";s:21:"margin_top_responsive";s:0:"";s:13:"margin_bottom";s:0:"";s:20:"margin_bottom_medium";s:0:"";s:24:"margin_bottom_responsive";s:0:"";s:11:"margin_left";s:0:"";s:18:"margin_left_medium";s:0:"";s:22:"margin_left_responsive";s:0:"";s:12:"margin_right";s:0:"";s:19:"margin_right_medium";s:0:"";s:23:"margin_right_responsive";s:0:"";s:18:"responsive_display";s:0:"";s:18:"visibility_display";s:0:"";s:26:"visibility_user_capability";s:0:"";s:9:"animation";s:0:"";s:15:"animation_delay";s:3:"0.0";s:2:"id";s:0:"";s:5:"class";s:0:"";s:4:"type";s:9:"rich-text";}}}'),
