nd time in the past 16 years that the electoral votes overturned the popular votes: the last time it led to George W. Bushs victory. Today it led to Donald J. Trumps.</span></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;">Although this is a gross simplification of the many complex factors at play here, these could be the most influential. This election was a fascinating race. Contrary to popular belief it was not a fight between two individuals. It was a fight between two systems of authority, two visions not only of America, but also of the world. The 2016 elections have exposed many sensitive issues within the system, from the electoral college, to immigration, that each side has dissected and brought to the surface.</span></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;">This election could be thought of as a fight between two extremes: conformity to the age old Establishment or the acceptance of a radical authoritative change.</span></p>";s:20:"text_selected_editor";s:7:"tinymce";s:5:"autop";b:1;s:12:"_sow_form_id";s:13:"588612d34bf5d";s:11:"panels_info";a:7:{s:5:"class";s:31:"SiteOrigin_Widget_Editor_Widget";s:3:"raw";b:0;s:4:"grid";i:0;s:4:"cell";i:0;s:2:"id";i:0;s:9:"widget_id";s:36:"b17b1e32-8088-4ae6-b871-1344024e07af";s:5:"style";a:1:{s:18:"background_display";s:6:"center";}}}}s:5:"grids";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:"cells";i:1;s:5:"style";a:0:{}}}s:10:"grid_cells";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"grid";i:0;s:6:"weight";i:1;}}}');
