(301, 1, '2017-01-17 09:50:45', '2017-01-17 09:50:45', '<h1>-Personal Timeline</h1>\r\n<h1><img class="wp-image-281 aligncenter" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png" sizes="(max-width: 761px) 100vw, 761px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-300x102.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2-768x262.png 768w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Untitled-2.png 984w" alt="" width="761" height="259"></h1>\r\n<h2>Life in Dubai</h2>\r\n<p>Born in the Newyork of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environement that encouraged innovation. The highrises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, the&nbsp;grand expos and the bussing steets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had. My family and I left Dubai in 2009 following the 2008 recession.<br>\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-287" src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" width="1003" height="194"></p>\r\n<h2>Life in Tunisia</h2>\r\n<p>Far the busy five-laned roads and the sky piercing buildings, the city of Sousse is a quiet and costal city in Tunisia. The quiet however did not remain for long. A year after I moved to Sousse the Tunisian Revolution, nicknamed the "Revolution of the Jasmines", broke out. I witnessed the protests, heard the gunfire and participated in protecting our neighbourhoud.</p>\r\n<p>Neither my studies nor my moral were hindered due to the move and the subsequent revolution. On the contrary they were strengthened.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone s