(382, 1, '2017-01-22 20:41:48', '2017-01-22 20:41:48', '\n	<h1 style="text-align: center;">I am a Tunisian-Egyptian born in Dubai</h1>\n<!-- If Left Or Right -->\n	<ul>\n				<li>\n						<!--date-->\n					Oct 19, 1997				 \n			<!--/.date-->\n						<!--Timline-Content-->\n				<!--icon-->\n				<!--/.icon-->\n					<!--Timline-Title-->\n					<h2>\n						Born in Dubai					</h2>\n					<!--/.Timline-Title-->\n					<!--Timline-description-->\n					<h2>Life in Dubai</h2><p>Born in the New York of the Middle East, I grew up in a multicultural environnement that encouraged innovation. The high-rises I would wake up to were, to me, a testament and a reminder of the capacities of the human intellect and the power of human ambition. The large scale projects, thegrand expos and the busing streets voiced the innovative spirit that Dubai, and consequently I, had. My family and I left Dubai in 2009 following the 2008 recession.</p><p><img src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png" sizes="(max-width: 1003px) 100vw, 1003px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-300x58.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dubai-Skyline-silhouette-2000x384-1024x197.png 1024w" width="1003" height="194" /></p>\n					<!--/.Timline-description-->\n			<!--/.Timline-Content-->\n		</li>\n				<li>\n						<!--date-->\n					Jul 15, 2008				 \n			<!--/.date-->\n						<!--Timline-Content-->\n				<!--icon-->\n				<!--/.icon-->\n					<!--Timline-Title-->\n					<h2>\n						Moved to Tunisia					</h2>\n					<!--/.Timline-Title-->\n					<!--Timline-description-->\n					<h2>Life in Tunisia</h2><p>Far the busy five-laned roads and the sky piercing buildings, the city of Sousse is a quiet and costal city in Tunisia. The quiet however did not remain for long. A year after I moved to Sousse the Tunisian Revolution, nicknamed the "Revolution of the Jasmines", broke out. I witnessed the protests, heard the gunfire and participated in protecting our neighborhood.</p><p>Neither my studies nor my moral were hindered due to the move and the subsequent revolution. On the contrary they were strengthened.</p><p><img src="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r-300x160.png 300w, http://localhost/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/logo-tunisie-2013_uk_r.png 425w" alt="" width="300" height="160" /></p>\n					<!--/.Timline-description-->\n			<!--/.Timline-Content-->\n		</li>\n				<li>\n						<!--date-->\n					Aug 25, 2016				 \n			<!--/.date-->\n						<!--Timline-Content-->\n				<!--icon-->\n				<!--/.icon-->\n					<!--Timline-Title-->\n					<h2>\n						Graduated Highschool / Moved to Cairo					</h2>\n					<!--/.Timline-Title-->\n					<!--Timline-description-->\n					<h2>Life inEgypt</h2><p>Despite having previously lived in and frequently visited Egypt, I did not truly discover what Egypt has to offer. Gaining acceptance to AUC triggered a process of discovering what I hitherto considered familiar. Underneath the political turmoil and economic instability is a thriving and diverse population that calls for unity and prosperity. I am still uncovering the secrets of Egypt. Who knows what I will discover?</p>\n					<!--/.Timline-description-->\n			<!--/.Timline-Content-->\n		</li>\n			</ul>\n', 'Background', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '361-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-22 20:41:48', '2017-01-22 20:41:48', '', 361, 'http://localhost/wp/2017/01/22/361-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
